   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="edition">
            <ab>
               <lb n="1"/>בעלפלס
                    <lb n="2"/>יתן
                    <lb n="3"/>שמעי
                </ab>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>Beelpeles (Lord of Weight) gave Shimhi.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Transcription form Myres (1914) with revisions. The word "שמעי" here is understood as a personal name of the dedicator, Shimhi, possibly a variant of the biblical name Simeon (שמעון), while Myres understood it as a verbial form from the root ש.מ.ע (heard). </p>
         </div>
